# TWBooks App Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development

# =============================================================================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================

# Vercel KV Configuration (for production deployment on Vercel)
# These variables are automatically provided by Vercel when you add a KV database
# to your project. You can find these values in your Vercel dashboard under
# Storage > [Your KV Database] > .env.local tab

# KV_URL=redis://your-kv-url
# KV_REST_API_URL=https://your-rest-api-url
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=your-auth-token
# KV_REST_API_READ_ONLY_TOKEN=your-readonly-token

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================

# For Local Development (SQLite):
# - No environment variables needed
# - Database file will be created at data/twbooks.db
# - Perfect for development and testing

# For Local Development (with KV testing):
# - Uncomment the KV_* variables above
# - Copy values from your Vercel KV database settings
# - App will use KV instead of SQLite locally

# For Production (Vercel):
# - Deploy your app to Vercel
# - Add a KV database in the Vercel dashboard:
#   1. Go to your project dashboard
#   2. Navigate to Storage tab
#   3. Click "Create Database" and select "KV"
#   4. Follow the setup wizard
# - Vercel will automatically provide the KV environment variables
# - Redeploy your app to use KV storage

# =============================================================================
# ADDITIONAL NOTES
# =============================================================================

# Database Switching Logic:
# - If KV_URL, KV_REST_API_URL, and KV_REST_API_TOKEN are all present: Use KV
# - Otherwise: Use SQLite
# 
# This allows seamless switching between:
# - Local development (SQLite)
# - Local KV testing (KV with env vars)  
# - Production deployment (KV on Vercel)

# Next.js Configuration:
# - Environment variables starting with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are exposed to the browser
# - Database credentials are server-side only (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix)
# - Vercel automatically encrypts environment variables in production